{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857711263,"sessionID":"ses_286a21feaffemiSa5UqEr03IFE","part":{"id":"prt_d795e33ad001JL6xJrA98iYOz5","messageID":"msg_d795e250f001W4wIy9SqlHPQGP","sessionID":"ses_286a21feaffemiSa5UqEr03IFE","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_881a36443c934185957c57e0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\n2: \n3: ## Module\n4: `pkg/store`\n5: \n6: ## Language\n7: Go\n8: \n9: ## Size\n10: S\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirement: Valkey provider selection\n15: \n16: The system SHALL support Valkey as a store backend when `STORE_TYPE` is set to `valkey` (case-insensitive).\n17: \n18: ### Scenario: Valkey provider selected\n19: \n20: - **GIVEN** environment variable `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n21: - **WHEN** `Storage()` is first called\n22: - **THEN** the Valkey implementation is initialized\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## Requirement: Valkey client initialization\n27: \n28: The system SHALL create a Valkey client using `valkey-go` library with address and password from environment variables.\n29: \n30: ### Scenario: Valkey client created with multiple addresses\n31: \n32: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=valkey-node-1:6379,valkey-node-2:6379` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD=secret`\n33: - **WHEN** Valkey store initializes\n34: - **THEN** client is created with `InitAddress: [\"valkey-node-1:6379\", \"valkey-node-2:6379\"]` and `Password: \"secret\"`\n35: \n36: ### Scenario: Valkey client with cache disabled\n37: \n38: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true` and valid `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\n39: - **WHEN** Valkey options are built\n40: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is set to `true` on the client options\n41: \n42: ### Scenario: Valkey client with single client mode\n43: \n44: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true` and valid `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\n45: - **WHEN** Valkey options are built\n46: - **THEN** `ForceSingleClient` is set to `true` on the client options\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## Requirement: Valkey Ping operation\n51: \n52: The system SHALL verify Valkey connectivity by sending PING command and expecting \"PONG\" response.\n53: \n54: ### Scenario: Ping successful\n55: \n56: - **GIVEN** a running Valkey server\n57: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called on Valkey store\n58: - **THEN** command `B().Ping()` returns string \"PONG\"\n59: \n60: ### Scenario: Ping fails on disconnected server\n61: \n62: - **GIVEN** Valkey server is unavailable\n63: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n64: - **THEN** error is returned indicating connection failure\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## Requirement: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID\n69: \n70: The system SHALL retrieve sandbox JSON by session key using GET command.\n71: \n72: ### Scenario: Session found\n73: \n74: - **GIVEN** key `session:test-session` exists with valid JSON in Valkey\n75: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"test-session\")` is called\n76: - **THEN** returns `*types.SandboxInfo` with data unmarshaled from JSON\n77: \n78: ### Scenario: Session not found\n79: \n80: - **GIVEN** key `session:missing-session` does not exist in Valkey\n81: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"missing-session\")` is called\n82: - **THEN** returns `ErrNotFound` (detected via `IsValkeyNil`)\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## Requirement: Valkey StoreSandbox\n87: \n88: The system SHALL store sandbox JSON using SETNX and update both ZSET indexes in one DoMulti batch.\n89: \n90: ### Scenario: Store new sandbox\n91: \n92: - **GIVEN** a valid `*types.SandboxInfo` with `SessionID=newsession` and `ExpiresAt` set\n93: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n94: - **THEN** executes DoMulti with: SETNX `session:newsession`, ZADD to `session:expiry`, ZADD to `session:last_activity`\n95: \n96: ### Scenario: Store sandbox with zero ExpiresAt\n97: \n98: - **GIVEN** `*types.SandboxInfo` with `ExpiresAt` set to zero time\n99: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n100: - **THEN** error indicates invalid expiration time\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 280. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\n\n## Module\n`pkg/store`\n\n## Language\nGo\n\n## Size\nS\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Valkey provider selection\n\nThe system SHALL support Valkey as a store backend when `STORE_TYPE` is set to `valkey` (case-insensitive).\n\n### Scenario: Valkey provider selected\n\n- **GIVEN** environment variable `STORE_TYPE=valkey`","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775857711247,"end":1775857711261}}}}
